> These tasty little treats are perfect for satisfying cravings on the go. Wholesome chocolate and peanut butter–packed oat bites hit all the right notes. Whether you missed breakfast, need a quick snack, or are just feeling the urge to treat yourself, you're in luck!

Boil your kettle (or a #pot{} of water).

Bash the @peanuts{40%grams} finely with a #rolling pin{} or heavy pot.

Pop the @peanut butter{2%sachet}s and @chocolate chips{100%grams} into a #bowl{} and place on top of the #pot{}. Stir until melted.

Remove the bowl from the heat, stir in @oats{60%grams}, @sesame seeds{1%sachet} and a pinch of @salt{to taste}.

Mix until evenly distributed.

Transfer mixture to the #refrigerator{} and chill, uncovered, for ~{5-10%minutes}.

> Be careful not to over-chill—the mixture will become too hard to roll!

Once cool enough to handle, roll the mixture into 8-10 small balls.

Toss the bites in the bashed peanuts to cover well with the nuts.